   			    The Swarm Team

The Swarm project is based at the Swarm Development Group (SDG), in
Santa Fe, New Mexico.

The Swarm project was initiated by Chris Langton.  Roger Burkhart
(John Deere), Nelson Minar (now at Google), Glen Ropella (now at
Icarian), Manor Askenazi (now at Coopers & Lybrand), Irene Lee,
Vladimir Jojic (UIUC), and Alex Lancaster (UC Berkeley, formerly of
SFI) have all been active in the design and programming of Swarm.
Marcus Daniels is the current maintainer and lead developer at the
SDG.
